    dc:creator "Liao, Chengqing; Ohshima, Issei; Huang, Guohua" ;
    dc:date "2019" ;
    dc:title "A new leaf-mining moth, Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. (Lepidoptera: Gracillariidae: Gracillariinae) feeding on Aesculus chinensis Bunge (Hippocastanaceae) from China" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647176>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647180>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647182>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647184>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647186>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647188> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647176>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. A: Male adult (Qinling, Shaanxi), holotype, scale bar 2 mm. B: Female adult (Badagongshan, Hunan), paratype. C: Wings venation, scale bar 1mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647176/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647180>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. A: Male genitalia and coremata on abdominal segments VII and VIII. B: Male genitalia in dorsal view, with phallus removed. C: Right valva, inner view. D: Aedeagus. E: Middle part of phallus with cornuti. Scale bar 0.25 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647180/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647182>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. A: Female genitalia. B: Apical part. C: Signum. Scale bar 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647182/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647184>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Biology of Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. A: Habitat and host plant Aesculus chinensis in Huameiguan. B: Mine of first instar larvae. C: Mine of third instar larvae. D: The same mine of C with transmitted light. E-F: The lateral margin (E) or the apical part (F) of a leaflet folded downward by later instar larva inside. G. Leaf shelter (stacking two leaflets) of later instars larva indicated by white row. H: Inside of the leaflet shelter as shown in G. I: Transparent cocoon along the midrib on the underside of leaflet. J: Larva spinning cocoon. Scale bar 1 cm, except 0.5 cm in J." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647184/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647186>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. External morphology of Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. larva. Early sap-feeding (A-E) and final tissue-feeding(F-M) instar larvae. A: Dorsal view of head. B: Antenna. C: Apical part of labiomaxillary complex, ventrally. D: Labrum. E: Mandible. F: Larval chaetotaxy of final instar larva. G: Dorsal view of head. H: Ventral view. I: Dorsal view of abdominal segments 8-10. J: Antenna. K. Ventral view of labiomaxillary complex. L: Mandible. M: Labrum, dorsal and ventral." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647186/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.2647188>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. External morphology of Caloptilia aesculi, sp. nov. pupa. A: Dorsal view. B: Ventral view, male. C: Ventral view of A7–10, female. D: Lateral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/2647188/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

